# waveHub — Local Cursor Context

`CODE_STANDARDS.md` at the monorepo root is the single source of truth for
coding standards, quality gates, architecture rules, and package usage.

Do not duplicate standards in this file. If anything here conflicts with
`CODE_STANDARDS.md`, follow `CODE_STANDARDS.md`.

## Local addendum (wavehub-specific only)

- Keep SDK-facing changes backward compatible unless the change is intentionally
  versioned and documented in release notes.
- Run package-local tests/lint before commit in the touched wavehub package
  (`gnarly-sdk`, `aerial-runner`, `quiver-langchain`, or `shaka-mcp`).
- Do not hardcode version strings; use the repo `VERSION` and sync scripts.
